The paper proposes a new type of query for retrieving sets of objects that represent regions of space that may be of interest to the user. This involves techniques such as density-based clustering, spatial gridded posting lists, and fast range query algorithms. These techniques are commonly used in information retrieval (cs.IR), databases (cs.DB), natural language processing (cs.CL), data structures (cs.DS), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Therefore, these are the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper.
